      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\\\docs\\\\ARCHITECTURE.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\ARCHITECTURE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # System Architecture\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: LAMPForge follows a **client-heavy architecture** where the browser is the primary compute surface. All code generation, SQL execution, and evidence logging happen client-side. The only server-side component is the AI blueprint generation edge function.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## High-Level Architecture\n10: \n11: ```mermaid\n12: graph TB\n13:     subgraph \"Browser Runtime\"\n14:         direction TB\n15:         \n16:         subgraph \"Pages\"\n17:             LP[LandingPage.tsx<br/>Intent + Scaffold]\n18:             PDE[PDEPage.tsx<br/>Unified PDE]\n19:             CP[CanvasPage.tsx<br/>Standalone Canvas]\n20:             WBP[WorkbenchPage.tsx<br/>Standalone Workbench]\n21:             EVP[EvidencePage.tsx<br/>Standalone Evidence]\n22:         end\n23:         \n24:         subgraph \"Code Generation Engine\"\n25:             SG[sql-generator.ts<br/>DDL + PHP + HTML]\n26:             FT[forge-types.ts<br/>Zod Schemas]\n27:         end\n28:         \n29:         subgraph \"AI Pipeline\"\n30:             FA[forge-ai.ts<br/>3-Stage Inference]\n31:         end\n32:         \n33:         subgraph \"IDE Surface (3-Tier)\"\n34:             COF[CodeOSSFrame.tsx<br/>Tier Detection]\n35:             OVS[OpenVSCode Server<br/>Tier 1 - Primary]\n36:             COS[Static Code-OSS<br/>Tier 2 - Legacy]\n37:             WCE[WebContainerEditor.tsx<br/>Tier 3 - Fallback]\n38:             VB[vscode-bridge.ts<br/>PostMessage + Config]\n39:             WCP[webcontainer-project.ts<br/>Project Builder]\n40:         end\n41:         \n42:         subgraph \"Panels\"\n43:             CLIP[CLIPanel.tsx<br/>Command Registry]\n44:             SQLP[SQLWorkbenchPanel.tsx<br/>sql.js + SQLite WASM]\n45:             EVPP[EvidencePanel.tsx<br/>Timeline View]\n46:             PTB[PanelToggleBar.tsx<br/>Visibility Controls]\n47:         end\n48:         \n49:         subgraph \"Canvas Nodes\"\n50:             EN[EntityNode.tsx]\n51:             TN[TransactionNode.tsx]\n52:             ON[OracleNode.tsx]\n53:             FSN[ForgeStatusNode.tsx]\n54:         end\n55:         \n56:         subgraph \"Communication\"\n57:             PDC[pde-channel.ts<br/>BroadcastChannel]\n58:         end\n59:     end\n60:     \n61:     subgraph \"Edge (Serverless)\"\n62:         EF[forge-schema/<br/>Edge Function]\n63:         AG[Lovable AI Gateway<br/>Gemini 3 Flash]\n64:     end\n65:     \n66:     subgraph \"Optional Local\"\n67:         OL[Ollama / Foundry Local<br/>Phi-4-mini]\n68:     end\n69:     \n70:     LP --> FA\n71:     FA --> OL\n72:     FA --> EF\n73:     EF --> AG\n74:     \n75:     FA -->|\"ForgeBlueprint\"| PDE\n76:     PDE --> SG\n77:     SG --> COF\n78:     PDE --> CLIP\n79:     PDE --> SQLP\n80:     PDE --> EVPP\n81:     \n82:     COF --> VB\n83:     COF --> WCE\n84:     WCE --> WCP\n85:     \n86:     PDE --> CV[React Flow Canvas]\n87:     CV --> EN\n88:     CV --> TN\n89:     CV --> ON\n90:     CV --> FSN\n91:     \n92:     PDE --> PDC\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## Data Flow\n98: \n99: ### 1. Intent → Blueprint\n100: \n101: ```mermaid\n102: sequenceDiagram\n103:     participant U as User\n104:     participant LP as LandingPage\n105:     participant AI as AI Pipeline\n106:     participant V as Zod Validator\n107:     participant SS as sessionStorage\n108:     \n109:     U->>LP: Enter intent + select level\n110:     LP->>AI: forgeSchema(intent, level)\n111:     AI->>AI: tryOnnxRouter() → route?\n112:     AI->>AI: tryOnnxFallback() → blueprint?\n113:     alt ONNX success\n114:         AI-->>LP: {blueprint, provider: \"browser-native-onnx\"}\n115:     else ONNX unavailable/invalid\n116:         AI->>AI: tryArchRouter() → route\n117:         AI->>AI: tryFoundryLocal() → blueprint?\n118:         alt Local success\n119:             AI-->>LP: {blueprint, provider: \"foundry-local\"}\n120:         else Local unavailable\n121:             AI->>AI: tryCloudFallback()\n122:             AI-->>LP: {blueprint, provider: \"cloud\"}\n123:         end\n124:     end\n125:     LP->>V: validateBlueprint(raw)\n126:     V-->>LP: ForgeBlueprint (validated)\n127:     LP->>SS: Store blueprint + metadata\n128:     LP->>LP: navigate(\"/pde\")\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### 2. Blueprint → Code\n132: \n133: ```mermaid\n134: sequenceDiagram\n135:     participant PDE as PDEPage\n136:     participant SS as sessionStorage\n137:     participant SG as sql-generator\n138:     participant IDE as CodeOSSFrame\n139:     participant CV as Canvas\n140:     \n141:     PDE->>SS: Read blueprint\n142:     PDE->>CV: Populate entity/transaction nodes\n143:     PDE->>SG: generateAllFiles(blueprint)\n144:     SG-->>PDE: {sql/schema.sql, php/*.php, html/*.html}\n145:     PDE->>IDE: applyFsDiff(files)\n146:     IDE->>IDE: Write files to WebContainer/iframe\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### 3. Panel Undocking\n150: \n151: ```mermaid\n152: sequenceDiagram\n153:     participant PDE as PDEPage\n154:     participant BC as BroadcastChannel\n155:     participant TAB as New Browser Tab\n156:     \n157:     PDE->>PDE: User clicks undock icon\n158:     PDE->>BC: {type: \"panel-undocked\", panelId: \"sql\"}\n159:     PDE->>TAB: window.open(\"/pde/panel/sql\")\n160:     TAB->>BC: Subscribe to channel\n161:     Note over PDE,TAB: Panels communicate via BroadcastChannel\n162:     TAB->>BC: {type: \"panel-closed\", panelId: \"sql\"}\n163:     BC->>PDE: Panel returns to main view\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Component Relationships\n169: \n170: ### Page → Component Map\n171: \n172: | Page | Key Components |\n173: |------|---------------|\n174: | `LandingPage` | Template gallery, scaffold selector, intent textarea |\n175: | `PDEPage` | `CodeOSSFrame`, `CLIPanel`, `SQLWorkbenchPanel`, `EvidencePanel`, `PanelToggleBar`, React Flow canvas |\n176: | `CanvasPage` | React Flow canvas, `WebContainerEditor`, `TerminalPanel` |\n177: | `WorkbenchPage` | `CodeEditor` (Monaco), results table |\n178: | `EvidencePage` | Timeline cards, SDLC stage sidebar |\n179: \n180: ### Library → Consumer Map\n181: \n182: | Library | Consumed By |\n183: |---------|------------|\n184: | `forge-ai.ts` | `LandingPage` |\n185: | `forge-types.ts` | `forge-ai.ts`, `sql-generator.ts`, `pde-channel.ts`, `PDEPage`, `CanvasPage`, `CLIPanel`, `SQLWorkbenchPanel` |\n186: | `sql-generator.ts` | `PDEPage`, `CanvasPage`, `CLIPanel`, `SQLWorkbenchPanel` |\n187: | `vscode-bridge.ts` | `CodeOSSFrame` |\n188: | `pde-channel.ts` | `PDEPage`, `PDEPanelPage` |\n189: | `webcontainer-project.ts` | `WebContainerEditor` |\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ## Security Model\n194: \n195: | Layer | Mechanism |\n196: |-------|-----------|\n197: | **IDE iframe (OpenVSCode/Code-OSS)** | `sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-forms\"` |\n198: | **PostMessage** | `lampforge:` prefix validation via `isLampforgeMessage()` |\n199: | **Edge Function** | CORS headers, API key via `LOVABLE_API_KEY` env var |\n200: | **Generated PHP** | CSRF tokens, PDO prepared statements (at Exemplary/RAD levels) |\n201: | **Cross-Origin Isolation** | `COEP: require-corp`, `COOP: same-origin` headers in Vite config |\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Deployment Tiers\n206: \n207: LAMPForge operates across four deployment tiers, from most capable to most constrained. The same `.forge` file works across all tiers; the PDE adapts automatically.\n208: \n209: | Tier | Environment | IDE | Database | AI Inference | Network |\n210: |------|-------------|-----|----------|-------------|---------|\n211: | **1** | GitHub Codespaces / Cloud | OpenVSCode Server | Real MySQL | Cloud providers | Required |\n212: | **2** | Docker / devcontainer | OpenVSCode Server | Real MySQL | Foundry Local | Not required after pull |\n213: | **3** | Native runtime (USB) | Code-OSS / OpenVSCode | Real MySQL (user-space) | Foundry Local / ONNX | Not required |\n214: | **4** | Browser-native (zero install) | WebContainers | wa-sqlite (WASM) | ONNX Runtime Web | Not required |\n215: \n216: ### Sovereign Browser Configuration\n217: \n218: For Tier 3 and 4 deployments, Edge is extracted to user-space with pre-configured flags:\n219: \n220: ```\n221: bootstrap.ps1 → Extract Edge MSI → Inject edge-preferences.json → Repackage-PDE.ps1\n222: ```\n223: \n224: Key flags: WebGPU, WebNN (DirectML), WASM baseline+tiering, SharedArrayBuffer, IsolatedWebApps, all telemetry disabled.\n225: \n226: See `runtime/launchers/` for platform-specific bootstrappers and launchers.\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## AI Inference Cascade\n231: \n232: The AI pipeline (`sdk/forge-ai.ts`) implements a 4-stage fallback, each wrapped by `FinOpsGuard`:\n233: \n234: ```mermaid\n235: graph LR\n236:     subgraph \"Stage 1: Browser-Native\"\n237:         ONNX[ONNX Runtime Web<br/>INT4 quantised model<br/>WebNN or WASM backend]\n238:     end\n239:     subgraph \"Stage 2: Local Server\"\n240:         FL[Foundry Local<br/>localhost inference]\n241:     end\n242:     subgraph \"Stage 3: Cloud\"\n243:         GQ[Groq API]\n244:     end\n245:     subgraph \"Stage 4: Cloud\"\n246:         CB[Cerebras API]\n247:     end\n248: \n249:     ONNX -->|timeout/fail| FL\n250:     FL -->|unavailable| GQ\n251:     GQ -->|unavailable| CB\n252: \n253:     FG[FinOps Guard] -.->|wraps every call| ONNX\n254:     FG -.-> FL\n255:     FG -.-> GQ\n256:     FG -.-> CB\n257: ```\n258: \n259: When `finops.budget.max_monthly_cloud: 0.00`, Stages 3 and 4 are never reached.\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## Communication Layers\n264: \n265: | Layer | API | Scope | Current Status |\n266: |-------|-----|-------|----------------|\n267: | **Same-window** | React state / context | Single tab | Implemented |\n268: | **Same-machine** | BroadcastChannel | Tabs/windows of same origin | Implemented |\n269: | **Classroom LAN** | WebRTC DataChannel | Peer-to-peer between browsers | Planned |\n270: | **Cross-network** | WebSocket (relay) | Server-assisted fallback | Planned |\n271: \n272: The progression from BroadcastChannel to WebRTC DataChannel enables multiplayer features (pair programming, teacher observation) using the same message protocol with a different transport.\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: *This document is part of the LAMPForge doc-as-code suite. See [README.md](../README.md) for the full documentation index.*\n\n(End of file - total 276 lines)\n</content>",
