      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\curriculum\\05-lampforge-sdtp\\01-understanding-forge-protocol.forge</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: protocol: forge/1.0\n2: type: lesson\n3: \n4: metadata:\n5:   id: understanding-forge-protocol\n6:   title: \"Understanding the .forge Protocol\"\n7:   description: |\n8:     Introduction to the Software-Defined Training Protocol (SDTP) and\n9:     the .forge file format. Understand the philosophy and architecture.\n10:   duration_minutes: 35\n11:   difficulty: beginner\n12:   order: 1\n13: \n14: objectives:\n15:   - understand: \"What SDTP and .forge files are\"\n16:   - understand: \"The protocol vs implementation distinction\"\n17:   - understand: \"The five protocol layers\"\n18:   - identify: \"Real-world use cases\"\n19: \n20: steps:\n21:   - type: explain\n22:     id: what-is-sdtp\n23:     title: \"What is SDTP?\"\n24:     content: |\n25:       # Software-Defined Training Protocol\n26: \n27:       SDTP is a **protocol specification** for defining pedagogical\n28:       development experiences. It's like OpenAPI for learning environments.\n29: \n30:       ```\n31:       ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n32:       │                      Traditional LMS                        │\n33:       │                                                             │\n34:       │   Content locked in proprietary format                      │\n35:       │   Vendor-specific runtime                                   │\n36:       │   No portability between platforms                          │\n37:       └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n38: \n39:       ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40:       │                      SDTP Approach                          │\n\n(Showing lines 1-40 of 249. Use offset=41 to continue.)\n</content>",
