      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\curriculum\\05-lampforge-sdtp\\02-writing-your-first-forge-file.forge</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: protocol: forge/1.0\n2: type: lesson\n3: \n4: metadata:\n5:   id: writing-your-first-forge-file\n6:   title: \"Writing Your First .forge File\"\n7:   description: |\n8:     Hands-on creation of a .forge file from scratch. Understand\n9:     YAML syntax and required fields.\n10:   duration_minutes: 30\n11:   difficulty: beginner\n12:   order: 2\n13: \n14: objectives:\n15:   - apply: \"Create a basic .forge file structure\"\n16:   - apply: \"Define metadata and intent\"\n17:   - apply: \"Validate .forge file syntax\"\n18:   - understand: \"Required vs optional fields\"\n19: \n20: steps:\n21:   - type: explain\n22:     id: yaml-basics\n23:     title: \"YAML Basics for .forge\"\n24:     content: |\n25:       # YAML Syntax Refresher\n26: \n27:       .forge files use YAML (YAML Ain't Markup Language).\n28: \n29:       ```yaml\n30:       # Key-value pairs\n31:       key: value\n32: \n33:       # Nested structures (use 2-space indent)\n34:       parent:\n35:         child: value\n36:         another: value\n37: \n38:       # Lists\n39:       items:\n40:         - first\n\n(Showing lines 1-40 of 199. Use offset=41 to continue.)\n</content>",
