      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Now I have a thorough picture. Let me compile the full summary.\n\n---\n\n## LAMPForge Project - Search Results Summary\n\n### What is LAMPForge?\n\nLAMPForge is a **Pedagogical Development Environment (PDE)** -- a cognitive engineering platform that transforms how A-Level Digital Technology students (WJEC/Eduqas Unit 4) learn database-driven web development. Instead of manually configuring XAMPP, phpMyAdmin, and wrestling with SQL/PHP boilerplate, students **declare their intent in plain English** and LAMPForge translates that into normalized database schemas (1NF to 3NF+), PHP CRUD operations at four scaffold levels (Exploratory through RAD 2.0), Bootstrap-powered HTML forms, and a live-editable in-browser IDE. It is also the reference implementation of the **Software-Defined Training Protocol (SDTP)** -- an open protocol specification for declarative, cost-governed, curriculum-aligned learning environments defined via `.forge` files.\n\nThe project features a **client-heavy architecture** where the browser is the primary compute surface: all code generation, SQL execution (via sql.js/WASM), and evidence logging happen client-side, with a triage AI inference pipeline (ONNX Runtime Web -> Foundry Local -> Groq -> Cerebras) and an optional serverless edge function for blueprint generation. It was submitted as an academic coursework project for WJEC/Eduqas A-Level Digital Technology Unit 4 and also submitted to the **Royal Academy of Engineering (RAEng) Regional Talent Engines** programme, with a technical report documenting innovative INT4 quantization and \"Architectural Masquerading\" techniques for running AI inference on resource-constrained educational hardware.\n\n### Languages Used\n\nThe project is written primarily in:\n\n| Language | Where |\n|----------|-------|\n| **TypeScript (.ts)** | SDK core (`sdk/`), PDE library modules (`src/lib/`) |\n| **TypeScript React (.tsx)** | All UI pages, components, and panels (`src/pages/`, `src/components/`) |\n| **JavaScript/ES Modules (.mjs)** | CLI tooling (`cli/`), build scripts, ONNX runtime bundles (`public/ort.*.mjs`) |\n| **HTML** | Documentation site (`docs/`), PDE entry point (`index.html`) |\n| **CSS** | Documentation styling (`docs/styles.css`) |\n| **YAML (.forge)** | Curriculum lessons (`curriculum/`), examples (`examples/`) |\n| **JSON** | Configuration, schemas, manifests |\n| **Shell script (.sh / .cmd)** | Launcher scripts (`launch-lampforge.sh`, `launch-lampforge.cmd`) |\n| **Go** | Supervisor runtime (mentioned in `RUNTIME-ARCHITECTURE.md` for the native supervisor binary) -- no `.go` files found in the tree |\n| **Python** | Referenced in R&D docs (`python_oci_backend_architecture.md`) for an OCI backend -- no `.py` files found in the project root |\n\n### Main Source Files & Folders Found\n\nAll paths below are under:\n`C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\`\n\n**Top-level documentation:**\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `README.md` | Main project README (800 lines) - full overview, architecture, getting started |\n| `RAEng_Technical_Report_Local_AI_Optimization.md` | RAEng technical report on INT4 quantization and Architectural Masquerading |\n| `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` | System architecture, component relationships, data flow |\n| `docs/RUNTIME-ARCHITECTURE.md` | Runtime bundle architecture (MySQL/Caddy/PHP-CGI supervisor) |\n| `docs/SOVEREIGN_ARCHITECTURE_INSIGHTS.md` | Zero-infrastructure & hardware-abstraction insights |\n| `docs/SOVEREIGN_SCENARIOS.md` | User stories driving the architecture |\n| `docs/PLATFORM_IDENTITY.md` | Protocol history, SDTP definition, nomenclature |\n| `docs/RATIONALE.md` | Design rationale |\n| `docs/ROADMAP.md` | Feature roadmap |\n| `docs/USER-JOURNEYS.md` | User journey maps |\n| `docs/SCIENCE_OF_SNAPPINESS.md` | MoSCoW constraints for IDE native latency |\n| `docs/SOVEREIGN_MCP_IDENTITY.md` | Decentralized identity for MCP |\n| `docs/COGNITIVE_TAXONOMY_PROTOCOL.md` | Visual grammar of code taxonomy |\n| `docs/DESIGN-TOKEN-AUDIT.md` | Design token consistency audit |\n\n**Protocol Specification (`spec/`):**\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `spec/SPECIFICATION.md` | Full `.forge` protocol field-by-field specification |\n| `spec/GRAMMAR.md` | Complete EBNF formal grammar |\n| `spec/SCHEMA.json` | Draft 2020-12 JSON Schema |\n| `spec/LIFECYCLE.md` | 9-stage lifecycle with sequence diagrams |\n| `spec/FINOPS.md` | Cost model, enforcement, JSONL ledger format |\n| `spec/SECURITY.md` | Security model specification |\n\n**SDK (`sdk/`):**\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `sdk/forge-protocol.ts` | Zod schema + parser + validator |\n| `sdk/forge-types.ts` | Shared TypeScript types (ForgeBlueprint) |\n| `sdk/forge-ai.ts` | AI cascade router (ONNX -> local -> cloud) |\n| `sdk/forge-finops.ts` | FinOps ledger + guard |\n| `sdk/forge-onnx.ts` | Browser-native ONNX inference wrapper |\n| `sdk/forge-config.ts` | Config persistence helpers |\n| `sdk/forge-logger.ts` | Structured log emitter |\n| `sdk/forge-tokenizer.ts` | Token counting for FinOps budget tracking |\n| `sdk/forge-protocol-loader.ts` | Config resolution (URL param -> storage -> default) |\n| `sdk/forge-nano-warmer.ts` | Model warming utility |\n| `sdk/forge-ai-logic.ts` | AI logic helpers |\n\n**CLI (`cli/`):**\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `cli/forge-cli.mjs` | Main CLI entry point |\n| `cli/commands/init.mjs` | Interactive .forge generator |\n| `cli/commands/validate.mjs` | Schema validation |\n| `cli/commands/preview.mjs` | Preview generated SQL/PHP/HTML |\n| `cli/commands/examples.mjs` | List and copy example .forge files |\n| `cli/commands/curriculum.mjs` | Curriculum management |\n| `cli/banner.mjs` | ASCII banner |\n\n**PDE Source (`src/`):**\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `src/pages/LandingPage.tsx` | Intent declaration + scaffold selector |\n| `src/pages/PDEPage.tsx` | Unified PDE with